This README will provide instructions on how to compile saver_output.c for replay on a QNN backend

Setup:
------
Set QNN_SDK_ROOT by running 'source <QNN_SDK_PATH>/target/x86_64-linux-clang/bin/envsetup.sh'

To compile for x86 targets:
Ensure clang is discoverable in your PATH by running 'source <QNN_SDK_ROOT>/target/x86_64-linux-clang/bin/check-linux-dependency.sh'

To compile for android targets:
Set ANDROID_NDK_ROOT to the path of the Android NDK

To compile for DSP/HTP backends on aarch64:
Set HEXAGON_SDK_ROOT by running 'source <HEXAGON_SDK_PATH>/setup_sdk_env.source'

Compiling saver_output.c:
------------------
Ensure saver_output.c is in the same directory as Makefile, and run:

1) 'make all' to compile for all backends on x86 and android targets.

2) 'make x86' to compile for all backends on x86 targets.

3) 'make arm' to compile for all backends on arm targets.

4) 'make aarch64' to compile for all backends on aarch64 targets.

5) 'make <backend>_<target>' to compile for a certain backend on a certain target. Valid options
   for <target> are x86, aarch, or arm. Valid options for <backend> are cpu or htp for <target>=x86,
   and cpu, gpu, dsp, or htp for <target>=arm or aarch64.

